 <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">Development of a low-noise readout ASIC for Silicon Drift Detectors in high energy resolution X-ray spectrometry</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">IOP</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">ASIC with a low-noise readout channel for Silicon Drift Detectors in high energy resolution X-ray spectrometry was designed and prototyped in the AMS 350 nm CMOS process via Europractice as a miniASIC. For the analog readout channel tests there was used the detector module SDD-10-130-PTW LTplus-ic (PNDetector GmbH). The measured energy resolution of this module with the designed readout channel: 200 eV (FWHM) at (55)Fe, -16 °C, 1 kcps and a peaking time of 8 μs.</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">IOP</subfield>
 </datafield>
